-- KNOWN LIMITATION tripwire (and termination regression). This match is
-- genuinely partial — e.g. `W (JUST 1) NOTHING TRUE` has no arm — but the
-- missing-branch analysis stays silent: `normalizeRefinement` collapses the
-- whole uncovered DISJUNCTION into a single constraint set (`Nabla`'s
-- Semigroup unions disjuncts), an approximation that under-detects multi-
-- branch nested misses and under-enumerates multi-field ones. See the
-- "deferred" notes in specs/todo/consider-exhaustiveness-scope-hardening.md.
-- This exact shape used to HANG the type-checker outright, so this fixture
-- pins both (a) termination and (b) the current, knowingly-incomplete
-- detection; if detection ever improves, this file should start failing and
-- must then move to not-ok/tc with a proper missing-branch golden.
DECLARE W
  HAS a IS A MAYBE OF NUMBER
      b IS A MAYBE OF MAYBE OF NUMBER
      c IS A BOOLEAN

GIVEN w IS A W
GIVETH A NUMBER
f w MEANS
  CONSIDER w
  WHEN W (JUST p) (JUST (JUST q)) FALSE THEN 1
  WHEN W NOTHING NOTHING TRUE THEN 0

#EVAL f (W (JUST 1) (JUST (JUST 2)) FALSE)
